  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Bariatric surgery has been reported to be the most effective treatment option for losing and&#xD;
      maintaining body weight and improving comorbidities and mortality associated with morbid&#xD;
      obesity. Nevertheless, even though physical activity is recommended to optimize bariatric&#xD;
      surgery results. Very little is known, about whether engaging in an exercise program after&#xD;
      surgery can provide additional improvement in health outcomes. While to date there are&#xD;
      relatively few researches studied the effect of exercise in patients who have undergone&#xD;
      bariatric surgery.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This study will investigate the effect of core stabilization exercise on patients who&#xD;
      underwent bariatric suergery.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
